''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine each year releases a Top [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]] songs of the year, counted from the first week of November to the final week in October.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2009/hot-100-songs |title=Year End Charts - Year-end songs - The Billboard Hot 100 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Nielsen CompanyNielsen Business Media, Inc]] |date= |accessdate=2009-12-11}} {{dead link|date=March 2013}}</ref> The [[2009 in music|2009]] list was dominated by [[The Black Eyed Peas]] and [[Lady Gaga]], who shared the top four spots. On 27 December, [[DJ Earworm]] released a [[Mashup (music)|mashup]] video to YouTube entitled "Blame It On The Pop", featuring the top twenty-five songs from the list, as he had also done the previous two years. The video quickly went [[viral video|viral]], and received four million views in little over a week.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.macon.com/248/story/976100.html|title=Viral Video: 2009's Top 25 songs remixed|last=Smith|first=Mark W.|date=6 January 2010|work=[[The Telegraph (Macon)]]|accessdate=10 January 2010}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>
